# Local Install of PAWS #

This uses the jupyterhub docker spawner to install a fully functional
version of PAWS locally.

## Pre-requisites ##

1. A version of Docker installed
2. Your user must belong to the 'docker' group
3. Python 3.4+
4. VirtualEnv

## Install ##

1. `virtualenv -p python3 .`
2. `source bin/activate'
3. `pip install -r requirements.txt`
4. `jupyterhub`

This will start a PAWS installation that will use local docker
containers and PAM (aka your local machine's username/password).
